## Our Verdict

**Rating: ★★★★☆ 4.3/5**

The Easee One is a charger that gets the hardware absolutely right. The design is class-leading, the build quality is superb, the tethered/untethered flexibility is genuinely clever, and the multi-unit load balancing is the best in the business for multi-EV households and flats.

But the software lets it down. The lack of smart tariff integration is a meaningful gap in the UK market, where millions of EV drivers are on Octopus Intelligent Go, Agile, or similar tariffs. The Ohme Home Pro's automatic tariff optimisation can save £300–£500 per year — that's money the Easee simply can't save you.

**Buy the Easee One if:** You want the best-looking charger, need multi-unit load balancing (flats, shared parking, multi-EV homes), or value tethered/untethered flexibility. Also a strong choice if you're on a simple flat-rate tariff where smart tariff integration doesn't matter.

**Look elsewhere if:** You're on a smart electricity tariff and want automated charging optimisation. The [Ohme Home Pro](/reviews/ohme-home-pro-review/) is the clear winner there. If solar is your priority, the [myenergi Zappi](/reviews/zappi-v2-review/) handles it better natively.

